{"questionId":"12362","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A right circular cone of radius <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\">\n  <mi>r</mi>\n</math></span> is inscribed in a sphere with centre O and radius <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"R\">\n  <mi>R</mi>\n</math></span> as shown&nbsp;in the following diagram. The perpendicular height of the cone is <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\">\n  <mi>h</mi>\n</math></span>, X denotes the centre of&nbsp;its base and B a point where the cone touches the sphere.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/9689ae276e401f7cb5aab4f1e1cd0a9c884e020d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that the volume of the cone may be expressed by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V = \\frac{\\pi }{3}\\left( {2R{h^2} - {h^3}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>V</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p>attempt to use Pythagoras in triangle OXB&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" \\Rightarrow {r^2} = {R^2} - {\\left( {h - R} \\right)^2}\">\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substitution of their <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{r^2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>r</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> into formula for volume of cone&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"V = \\frac{{\\pi {r^2}h}}{3}\">\n  <mi>V</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>r</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mi>h</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{\\pi h}}{3}\\left( {{R^2} - {{\\left( {h - R} \\right)}^2}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mi>h</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>(</mo>\n              <mrow>\n                <mi>h</mi>\n                <mo>−</mo>\n                <mi>R</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mo>)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n          </mrow>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{\\pi h}}{3}\\left( {{R^2} - \\left( {{h^2} + {R^2} - 2hR} \\right)} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mi>h</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>(</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>h</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <msup>\n              <mi>R</mi>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </msup>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mi>R</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>)</mo>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> This <strong>A</strong> mark is independent and may be seen anywhere for the correct&nbsp;expansion of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{{{\\left( {h - R} \\right)}^2}}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msup>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>h</mi>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mi>R</mi>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msup>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{{\\pi h}}{3}\\left( {2hR - {h^2}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>π</mi>\n      <mi>h</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>h</mi>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\" = \\frac{\\pi }{3}\\left( {2R{h^2} - {h^3}} \\right)\">\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mi>π</mi>\n    <mn>3</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mi>R</mi>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mi>h</mi>\n          <mn>3</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"12362","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ2.H_8a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that the volume of the cone may be expressed by V = π 3 ( 2 R h 2 − h 3 ) .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.6—Stationary points, local max and min","Topic 5—Calculus","SL 5.7—Optimisation"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}